NARRATIVE:

    On 11/4/2023, while investigating MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-034584, I located IP logins for Google Account: bmotzdds@gmail.com that related to Leaseweb Virginia, which Motz previously advised were where Harscher had been logging into his Facebook. Motz provided that Harscher accessed his Facebook Account: https://www.facebook.com/brian.motz.9?mibextid=LQQJ4d (Brian Motz) and alleging that this proved that Harscher had stolen his laptop. For further details about the investigation, please refer to S/Tpr. Key's #6165 MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-027371. For details about Motz advising there was "proof" that Andria Sue Harscher (W/F 09/09/1981) had stolen Motz' laptop and logged into his Facebook Account, refer below to image below: 



    The above listed email from Motz to S/Tpr. Key, is referencing the below listed IP logins that Motz provided during the course of the "stolen" laptop investigation. Refer to images below:
    
    Motz went on to provide, to S/Tpr. Key, that he had conducted a search into IP address: 207.244.110.22. See image below:


    The IP address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe and IP address: 2601:148:201:8d0:54d9 are similar IP addresses logged into Motz' email address logins, Google Account: bmotzdds@gmail.com, which come back to Verizon Wireless and Comcasr Cable respectfully.

    Referring to Supplement #2 Narrative, of S/Tpr. Key's report (23-MSP-027371), I documented that I had conducted a search through Maxmind's database for IP address: 207.244.110.22, which came back to Arlington, Virginia and the Internet Service Provider (ISP) as Leaseweb Virginia. The IP address: 172.20.10.2 reported to be the last known IP address for the reported "stolen" laptop is a local IP address, which cannot be tracked. 

    While reviewing Motz' email address logins, Google Account: bmotzdds@gmail.com in reference to MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-034584,I observed the below listed logins:

It should be noted that Leaseweb Virginia is documented to be an ISP service and has been flagged as a potential fraud risk on public websites.

    On 11/4/2023 at approximately 1142 hours, I electronically submitted a Meta Platforms, Inc. Court Order, referencing Facebook Account: https://www.facebook.com/brian.motz.9?mibextid=LQQJ4d, and LeaseWeb USA Inc. Court Order to the Frederick County State's Attorney's Office for review and endorsement.

    On 11/6/2023 at approximately 1006 hours, I received the signed and endorsed Meta Platforms, Inc. Court Order, referencing Facebook Account: https://www.facebook.com/brian.motz.9?mibextid=LQQJ4d, and the signed and endorsed LeaseWeb USA Inc. Court Order from the Frederick County State's Attorney's Office.

    At approximately 1018 hours, I electronically submitted the signed and endorsed LeaseWeb USA Inc. Court Order to LeaseWeb USA Inc, via email address: subpoenas@us.leaseweb.com. At approximately 1122 hours, I received an email from LeaseWeb USA Inc. acknowledging receipt of the legal request.

    At approximately 1049 hours, I electronically submitted a Google Court Order, referencing Google Account: andriaharscher09@gmail.com, to the Frederick County State's Attorney's Office for review and endorsement.

    At approximately 1056 hours, I electronically submitted the signed and endorsed Meta Platforms, Inc. Court Order, referencing Facebook Account: https://www.facebook.com/brian.motz.9?mibextid=LQQJ4d. The request was assigned Case #: 8220025.

    At approximately 1438 hours, I contacted Dell Technologies and spoke with Dell Technologies' Global Fraud & Cyber Investigations Lead. I was advised that Dell was still currently unable to log IP addresses of the stolen black/gray Dell Lattitude 3520 (S/N: H0VB7S3).

    On 11/7/2023 at approximately 1016 hours, I made contact with a Help Desk Team Lead of DTC, formerly called Dental Technology Center, which is an IT company that services Monocacy Valley Dental. The Help Desk Team Lead provided that DTC provides clients such as Connectwise Manage and Connectwise Automate for Monocacy Valley Dental. The Help Desk Team Lead was familiar with Mr. Motz and the alleged "stolen" black/gray Dell Lattitude 3520 (S/N: H0VB7S3) as well as the HP laptop, that Healy advised she was only assigned from Monocacy Valley Dental. The Help Desk Team Lead provided that the only IP address(es) that DTC had been local IPs that could not be tracked. The Help Desk Team Lead did provide that he was familiar with Healy, because prior to the alleged theft of the laptop Healy was the Office Manager of Monocacy Valley Dental and was listed as the primary point of contact for the office, which explained why she would be referenced in ticket requests for DTC. The Help Desk Team Lead advised that Healy was no longer listed as active in the system and added that Motz is now the primary contact. The Help Desk Team Lead also provided the alleged "stolen" black/gray Dell Lattitude 3520 (S/N: H0VB7S3) was set for a remote wipe, if it were to come back onto network / connect to the internet, however as of the contact the laptop had not come online and/or flagged as coming online and was pending being taken out of the system for DTC given it had not been active since it was reported. 

    At approximately 1127 hours, I received the signed and endorsed Google Court Order, referencing Google Account: andriaharscher09@gmail.com, from the Frederick County State's Attorney's Office.

    At approximately 1208 hours, I contacted Healy and inquired about Monocacy Valley Dentals systems. Healy provided that patient information was accessed through a server and added that Motz had access to all employee emails and passwords at Monocacy Valley Dental. While reviewing the Google Search Warrant Return, in reference to Google Account: bmotzdds@gmail.com, from MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-034584, I observed Screenshot_20230729_161812_-1j621c8dip4gy.jpg, which is a Screenshot from Gusto, stating "Hi Lauren, Did you know that Brian K. Motz D.D.S., P.C. has created a former employee Gusto account for you? Even though you're no longer working there, you still have" and then the screenshot cuts off. The screenshot appears to be from an Android style smartphone. Screenshot: Screenshot_20230729_161831_-1j621oswei102.jpg was also located providing further/similar information. I also observed another image where Motz changed his profile to "Arthee Motz". Further information to come in a later supplement. 

    At approximately 1228 hours, I electronically submitted the signed and endorsed Google Court Order, referencing Google Account: andriaharscher09@gmail.com, to Google, via Google's Law Enforcement Request System. The request was assigned Google Reference. No. 46366771.

The case is remaining OPEN pending further investigation. 

Case Status: OPEN

NARRATIVE:

    On 11/20/2023 at approximately 1215 hours, I received an email from S/Tpr. Key with additional email correspondence from Motz in regard to his investigation, MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-027371.

    On 11/22/2023 at approximately 1128 hours, I received Verizon’s Subpoena Compliance, in reference to IP address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe on 07-30-2023 at 16:31:08 UTC hours. Verizon provided that there were not records for IP address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe on that date and time.

    At approximately 1201 hours, I emailed Motz' attorney, Caroline Frost, and offered Motz a polygraph examination in regard to this investigation.

    At approximately 1907 hours, I requested Verizon ensure that there were no records, which they complied with. 

    On 11/27/2023 at approximately 1000 hours, I received that another check was conducted, and no records were located.

    On 11/30/2023 at approximately 0743 hours, the Maryland State Police (MSP) Criminal Enforcement Division (CED) - Western Region Investigators along with the MSP Frederick Barrack executed a search warrant on Monocacy Valley Dental, 161 Thomas Johnson Dr, Ste 195, Frederick, MD 21702 in regard to MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-038907. Upon entering the target location, the following individuals were located within the establishment: Brian Kelly Motz (W/M 01/28/1980), Marlina Lynn Wolford (W/F 06/21/1964), Katrina S. Hoyt (W/F 09/13/1970), Ashley Marie Hamm (W/F 06/16/1998), Megan Amanda Baker (W/F 10/5/1995) as well as a patient. 

    During the course of the search warrant, I interviewed Ashley Hamm (W/F 06/16/1998). While speaking with Hamm, I asked her if any further documentation was ever located in regard to the alleged stolen laptop from the office, referencing MSP Case Numbers: 23-MSP-027371 & 23-MSP-038908. While speaking with Hamm, she acknowledged similar information provided from DTC that Healy signed for multiple electronic requests, given her office title/position. When I spoke with Hamm about email correspondence, she advised that she emailed me twice, adding that if it said her name, she hoped it was from her. Hamm did advise that Healy utilized the alleged stolen laptop for "morning huttles". Hamm also advised through various computer programs at the office, given Motz is the administrator, he has access to employees passwords, except for the Weve program. I later clarified with Hamm that the program that Healy was alleged to have logged into with the alleged stolen laptop, Motz would have had access to Healy's login/password information. I further asked Hamm if employees, including Hamm, had access to Motz' passwords, and she shook her head in the negative, adding that Motz had access to their passwords. The previously listed interaction was captured on my agency issued body worn camera. The previously listed interaction is a brief synopsis and not and exact transcription of all events that took place. For the entirety of interaction, please refer to the Axon recording uploaded to Evidence.com.

    On 12/18/2023 at approximately 1445 hours, I electronically submitted two Verizon Subpoenas, referencing IP Address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe, to the Frederick County State’s Attorney’s Office for review and endorsement. This IP address is the IP address that Verizon was unable to provide information on 11/22/2023 at approximately 1128 hours. This IP address specifically comes from Attachment: Original File Name: Screenshot_20230808_104743_Facebook.jpg of S/Tpr. Key’s Supplement #1 Narrative for MSP Case Number: 23-MSP-027371 where S/Tpr. Key documented that Motz forwarded him screenshots of Facebook/IP login information and alleged that Harscher had “hacked” into his Facebook account. The exact time for the login was obtained from Meta Platforms, Inc. Court Order Compliance of Facebook Account: https://www.facebook.com/brian.motz.9?mibextid=LQQJ4d.

    At approximately 1536 hours, I received the signed and endorsed Verizon Subpoenas, referencing IP Address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe, from the Frederick County State's Attorney's Office.

    At approximately 1625 hours, I electronically submitted the signed and endorsed Verizon Subpoenas, referencing IP Address: 2600:1003:b045:9e2d:3847:d25c:6d03:a1fe, to Verizon, via email address: VerizonLegalProcessCompliance@one.verizon.com.

    On 12/19/2023 at approximately 0848 hours, I emailed Ms. Frost to follow up about the requested polygraph examination and addressed three questions I would like asked, to include the following: 

        1.) Throughout the investigation of the alleged stolen laptop, have you (Motz) intentionally provided any information that you know to not be true or accurate, with the intention of misleading law enforcement?

        2.) For question 2, I would like Mr. Motz to identify the last location he was aware the laptop was located, and I would like it to be asked if that is a true statement. 

        3.) Have you (Motz) had any involvement in the laptops' disappearance?

The case is remaining OPEN pending further investigation.
